Title: RegulatingCondEq

Type

object

No

Additional properties

[Any type: allowed]

Description: A type of conducting equipment that can regulate a quantity (i.e. voltage or flow) at a specific point in the network.

Property

Pattern

Type

Deprecated

Definition

Title/Description

- PowerElectronicsConnection

No

object

No

In ./PowerElectronicsConnection.json

A connection to the AC network for energy production or consumption that uses power electronics rather than rotating machines.

- StaticVarCompensator

No

object

No

In ./StaticVarCompensator.json

A facility for providing variable and controllable shunt reactive power. The SVC typically consists of a stepdown transformer, filter, thyristor-controlled reactor, and thyristor-switched capacitor arms.



The SVC may operate in fixed MVar output mode or in voltage control mode. When in voltage control mode, the output of the SVC will be proportional to the deviation of voltage at the controlled bus from the voltage setpoint. The SVC characteristic slope defines the proportion. If the voltage at the controlled bus is equal to the voltage setpoint, the SVC MVar output is zero.

- ExternalNetworkInjection

No

object

No

In ./ExternalNetworkInjection.json

This class represents the external network and it is used for IEC 60909 calculations.

- FrequencyConverter

No

object

No

In ./FrequencyConverter.json

A device to convert from one frequency to another (e.g., frequency F1 to F2) comprises a pair of FrequencyConverter instances. One converts from F1 to DC, the other converts the DC to F2.

- ShuntCompensator

No

object

No

In ./ShuntCompensator.json

A shunt capacitor or reactor or switchable bank of shunt capacitors or reactors. A section of a shunt compensator is an individual capacitor or reactor. A negative value for bPerSection indicates that the compensator is a reactor. ShuntCompensator is a single terminal device. Ground is implied.

- RotatingMachine

No

object

No

In ./RotatingMachine.json

A rotating machine which may be used as a generator or motor.

1.3.1.1. Property RegulatingCondEq > PowerElectronicsConnection > ConductingEquipment.Terminals > Terminal > ACDCTerminal.connectedÂ¶

Title: connected

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The connected status is related to a bus-branch model and the topological node to terminal relation. True implies the terminal is connected to the related topological node and false implies it is not. In a bus-branch model, the connected status is used to tell if equipment is disconnected without having to change the connectivity described by the topological node to terminal relation. A valid case is that conducting equipment can be connected in one end and open in the other. In particular for an AC line segment, where the reactive line charging can be significant, this is a relevant case.

1.3.1.2. Property RegulatingCondEq > PowerElectronicsConnection > ConductingEquipment.Terminals > Terminal > Terminal.phasesÂ¶

Title: phases

Type

enum (of string)

Required

No

Defined in

./PhaseCode.json

Description: Represents the normal network phasing condition. If the attribute is missing, three phases (ABC) shall be assumed, except for terminals of grounding classes (specializations of EarthFaultCompensator, GroundDisconnector, and Ground) which will be assumed to be N. Therefore, phase code ABCN is explicitly declared when needed, e.g. for star point grounding equipment. The phase code on terminals connecting same ConnectivityNode or same TopologicalNode as well as for equipment between two terminals shall be consistent.

Must be one of:

  • âABCNâ

  • âABCâ

  • âABNâ

  • âACNâ

  • âBCNâ

1.3.1.5. Property RegulatingCondEq > PowerElectronicsConnection > ConductingEquipment.Terminals > Terminal > IdentifiedObject.aliasNameÂ¶

Title: aliasName

Type

string

Required

No

Description: The aliasName is free text human readable name of the object alternative to IdentifiedObject.name. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy. The attribute aliasName is retained because of backwards compatibility between CIM relases. It is however recommended to replace aliasName with the Name class as aliasName is planned for retirement at a future time.

1.3.1.6. Property RegulatingCondEq > PowerElectronicsConnection > ConductingEquipment.Terminals > Terminal > IdentifiedObject.mRIDÂ¶

Title: mRID

Type

string

Required

No

Description: Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended. For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

1.4.1.5. Property RegulatingCondEq > PowerElectronicsConnection > PowerElectronicsConnection.PowerElectronicsUnit > oneOf > BatteryUnit > Equipment.aggregateÂ¶

Title: aggregate

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The aggregate flag provides an alternative way of representing an aggregated (equivalent) element. It is applicable in cases when the dedicated classes for equivalent equipment do not have all of the attributes necessary to represent the required level of detail. In case the flag is set to âtrueâ the single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modelled together as an aggregate equivalent obtained by a network reduction procedure. Examples would be power transformers or synchronous machines operating in parallel modelled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine.
The attribute is not used for EquivalentBranch, EquivalentShunt and EquivalentInjection.

1.4.1.18. Property RegulatingCondEq > PowerElectronicsConnection > PowerElectronicsConnection.PowerElectronicsUnit > oneOf > BatteryUnit > IdentifiedObject.mRIDÂ¶

Title: mRID

Type

string

Required

No

Description: Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended. For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

1.7.1.1. Property RegulatingCondEq > PowerElectronicsConnection > ConductingEquipment.SvStatus > SvStatus > SvStatus.inServiceÂ¶

Title: inService

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The in service status as a result of topology processing. It indicates if the equipment is considered as energized by the power flow. It reflects if the equipment is connected within a solvable island. It does not necessarily reflect whether or not the island was solved by the power flow.

1.10. Property RegulatingCondEq > PowerElectronicsConnection > Equipment.aggregateÂ¶

Title: aggregate

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The aggregate flag provides an alternative way of representing an aggregated (equivalent) element. It is applicable in cases when the dedicated classes for equivalent equipment do not have all of the attributes necessary to represent the required level of detail. In case the flag is set to âtrueâ the single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modelled together as an aggregate equivalent obtained by a network reduction procedure. Examples would be power transformers or synchronous machines operating in parallel modelled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine.
The attribute is not used for EquivalentBranch, EquivalentShunt and EquivalentInjection.

1.11. Property RegulatingCondEq > PowerElectronicsConnection > Equipment.networkAnalysisEnabledÂ¶

Title: networkAnalysisEnabled

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The equipment is enabled to participate in network analysis. If unspecified, the value is assumed to be true.

1.12. Property RegulatingCondEq > PowerElectronicsConnection > Equipment.normallyInServiceÂ¶

Title: normallyInService

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: Specifies the availability of the equipment under normal operating conditions. True means the equipment is available for topology processing, which determines if the equipment is energized or not. False means that the equipment is treated by network applications as if it is not in the model.

1.27. Property RegulatingCondEq > PowerElectronicsConnection > IdentifiedObject.aliasNameÂ¶

Title: aliasName

Type

string

Required

No

Description: The aliasName is free text human readable name of the object alternative to IdentifiedObject.name. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy. The attribute aliasName is retained because of backwards compatibility between CIM relases. It is however recommended to replace aliasName with the Name class as aliasName is planned for retirement at a future time.

1.28. Property RegulatingCondEq > PowerElectronicsConnection > IdentifiedObject.mRIDÂ¶

Title: mRID

Type

string

Required

No

Description: Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended. For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

Title: name

string

Description: The name is any free human readable and possibly non unique text naming the object.

2. Property RegulatingCondEq > StaticVarCompensatorÂ¶

Type

object

Required

No

Additional properties

[Any type: allowed]

Defined in

./StaticVarCompensator.json

Description: A facility for providing variable and controllable shunt reactive power. The SVC typically consists of a stepdown transformer, filter, thyristor-controlled reactor, and thyristor-switched capacitor arms.

The SVC may operate in fixed MVar output mode or in voltage control mode. When in voltage control mode, the output of the SVC will be proportional to the deviation of voltage at the controlled bus from the voltage setpoint. The SVC characteristic slope defines the proportion. If the voltage at the controlled bus is equal to the voltage setpoint, the SVC MVar output is zero.

2.8. Property RegulatingCondEq > StaticVarCompensator > Equipment.aggregateÂ¶

Title: aggregate

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The aggregate flag provides an alternative way of representing an aggregated (equivalent) element. It is applicable in cases when the dedicated classes for equivalent equipment do not have all of the attributes necessary to represent the required level of detail. In case the flag is set to âtrueâ the single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modelled together as an aggregate equivalent obtained by a network reduction procedure. Examples would be power transformers or synchronous machines operating in parallel modelled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine.
The attribute is not used for EquivalentBranch, EquivalentShunt and EquivalentInjection.

3.26. Property RegulatingCondEq > ExternalNetworkInjection > Equipment.aggregateÂ¶

Title: aggregate

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The aggregate flag provides an alternative way of representing an aggregated (equivalent) element. It is applicable in cases when the dedicated classes for equivalent equipment do not have all of the attributes necessary to represent the required level of detail. In case the flag is set to âtrueâ the single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modelled together as an aggregate equivalent obtained by a network reduction procedure. Examples would be power transformers or synchronous machines operating in parallel modelled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine.
The attribute is not used for EquivalentBranch, EquivalentShunt and EquivalentInjection.

3.27. Property RegulatingCondEq > ExternalNetworkInjection > Equipment.networkAnalysisEnabledÂ¶

Title: networkAnalysisEnabled

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The equipment is enabled to participate in network analysis. If unspecified, the value is assumed to be true.

3.28. Property RegulatingCondEq > ExternalNetworkInjection > Equipment.normallyInServiceÂ¶

Title: normallyInService

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: Specifies the availability of the equipment under normal operating conditions. True means the equipment is available for topology processing, which determines if the equipment is energized or not. False means that the equipment is treated by network applications as if it is not in the model.

3.29. Property RegulatingCondEq > ExternalNetworkInjection > Equipment.inServiceÂ¶

Title: inService

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: Specifies the availability of the equipment. True means the equipment is available for topology processing, which determines if the equipment is energized or not. False means that the equipment is treated by network applications as if it is not in the model.

3.30. Property RegulatingCondEq > ExternalNetworkInjection > IdentifiedObject.aliasNameÂ¶

Title: aliasName

Type

string

Required

No

Description: The aliasName is free text human readable name of the object alternative to IdentifiedObject.name. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy. The attribute aliasName is retained because of backwards compatibility between CIM relases. It is however recommended to replace aliasName with the Name class as aliasName is planned for retirement at a future time.

3.31. Property RegulatingCondEq > ExternalNetworkInjection > IdentifiedObject.mRIDÂ¶

Title: mRID

Type

string

Required

No

Description: Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended. For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

3.32. Property RegulatingCondEq > ExternalNetworkInjection > IdentifiedObject.nameÂ¶

Title: name

Type

string

Required

No

Description: The name is any free human readable and possibly non unique text naming the object.

5.5.1.2. Property RegulatingCondEq > ShuntCompensator > ShuntCompensator.ShuntCompensatorPhase > ShuntCompensatorPhase > IdentifiedObject.aliasNameÂ¶

Title: aliasName

Type

string

Required

No

Description: The aliasName is free text human readable name of the object alternative to IdentifiedObject.name. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy. 5.5.1.3. Property RegulatingCondEq > ShuntCompensator > ShuntCompensator.ShuntCompensatorPhase > ShuntCompensatorPhase > IdentifiedObject.mRIDÂ¶

Title: mRID

Type

string

Required

No

Description: Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended. For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

5.5.1.4. Property RegulatingCondEq > ShuntCompensator > ShuntCompensator.ShuntCompensatorPhase > ShuntCompensatorPhase > ShuntCompensatorPhase.sectionsÂ¶

Title: sections

Type

number

Required

No

Description: Shunt compensator sections in use. Starting value for steady state solution. The attribute shall be a positive value or zero. Non integer values are allowed to support continuous variables. The reasons for continuous value are to support study cases where no discrete shunt compensators has yet been designed, a solutions where a narrow voltage band force the sections to oscillate or accommodate for a continuous solution as input. For LinearShuntConpensator the value shall be between zero and ShuntCompensatorPhase.maximumSections. At value zero the shunt compensator conductance and admittance is zero. Linear interpolation of conductance and admittance between the previous and next integer section is applied in case of non-integer values. For NonlinearShuntCompensator-s shall only be set to one of the NonlinearShuntCompenstorPhasePoint.sectionNumber. There is no interpolation between NonlinearShuntCompenstorPhasePoint-s.

5.26. Property RegulatingCondEq > ShuntCompensator > Equipment.aggregateÂ¶

Title: aggregate

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The aggregate flag provides an alternative way of representing an aggregated (equivalent) element. It is applicable in cases when the dedicated classes for equivalent equipment do not have all of the attributes necessary to represent the required level of detail. In case the flag is set to âtrueâ the single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modelled together as an aggregate equivalent obtained by a network reduction procedure. Examples would be power transformers or synchronous machines operating in parallel modelled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine.
The attribute is not used for EquivalentBranch, EquivalentShunt and EquivalentInjection.

5.27. Property RegulatingCondEq > ShuntCompensator > Equipment.normallyInServiceÂ¶

Title: normallyInService

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: Specifies the availability of the equipment under normal operating conditions. True means the equipment is available for topology processing, which determines if the equipment is energized or not. False means that the equipment is treated by network applications as if it is not in the model.

Type

combining

Required

No

Additional properties

[Any type: allowed]

Defined in

./GeneratingUnit.json

Description: A single or set of synchronous machines for converting mechanical power into alternating-current power. For example, individual machines within a set may be defined for scheduling purposes while a single control signal is derived for the set. In this case there would be a GeneratingUnit for each member of the set and an additional GeneratingUnit corresponding to the set.

One of(Option)

HydroGeneratingUnit.json

SolarGeneratingUnit.json

NuclearGeneratingUnit.json

WindGeneratingUnit.json

ThermalGeneratingUnit.json

Description: Governor Speed Changer Droop. A positive value of speed change droop provides additional generator output upon a drop in frequency.

6.5.1.34. Property RegulatingCondEq > RotatingMachine > RotatingMachine.GeneratingUnit > oneOf > HydroGeneratingUnit > Equipment.aggregateÂ¶

Title: aggregate

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The aggregate flag provides an alternative way of representing an aggregated (equivalent) element. It is applicable in cases when the dedicated classes for equivalent equipment do not have all of the attributes necessary to represent the required level of detail. In case the flag is set to âtrueâ the single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modelled together as an aggregate equivalent obtained by a network reduction procedure. Examples would be power transformers or synchronous machines operating in parallel modelled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine.
The attribute is not used for EquivalentBranch, EquivalentShunt and EquivalentInjection.

Title: normallyInService

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: Specifies the availability of the equipment under normal operating conditions. True means the equipment is available for topology processing, which determines if the equipment is energized or not. False means that the equipment is treated by network applications as if it is not in the model.

6.5.1.38. Property RegulatingCondEq > RotatingMachine > RotatingMachine.GeneratingUnit > oneOf > HydroGeneratingUnit > IdentifiedObject.mRIDÂ¶

Title: mRID

Type

string

Required

No

Description: Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended. For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

6.5.2.4. Property RegulatingCondEq > RotatingMachine > RotatingMachine.GeneratingUnit > oneOf > SolarGeneratingUnit > GeneratingUnit.governorSCDÂ¶

Title: governorSCD

Type

object or number

Required

No

Same definition as

InefficientBatteryUnit.efficiencyDischarge

Description: Governor Speed Changer Droop. This is the change in generator power output divided by the change in frequency normalized by the nominal power of the generator and the nominal frequency and expressed in percent and negated. A positive value of speed change droop provides additional generator output upon a drop in frequency.

6.5.2.30. Property RegulatingCondEq > RotatingMachine > RotatingMachine.GeneratingUnit > oneOf > SolarGeneratingUnit > Equipment.aggregateÂ¶

Title: aggregate

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The aggregate flag provides an alternative way of representing an aggregated (equivalent) element. It is applicable in cases when the dedicated classes for equivalent equipment do not have all of the attributes necessary to represent the required level of detail. In case the flag is set to âtrueâ the single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modelled together as an aggregate equivalent obtained by a network reduction procedure. Examples would be power transformers or synchronous machines operating in parallel modelled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine.
The attribute is not used for EquivalentBranch, EquivalentShunt and EquivalentInjection.

Title: mRID

Type

string

Required

No

Description: Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended. For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

6.5.3.4. Property RegulatingCondEq > RotatingMachine > RotatingMachine.GeneratingUnit > oneOf > NuclearGeneratingUnit > GeneratingUnit.governorSCDÂ¶

Title: governorSCD

Type

object or number

Required

No

Same definition as

InefficientBatteryUnit.efficiencyDischarge

Description: Governor Speed Changer Droop. This is the change in generator power output divided by the change in frequency normalized by the nominal power of the generator and the nominal frequency and expressed in percent and negated. A positive value of speed change droop provides additional generator output upon a drop in frequency.

6.5.3.30. Property RegulatingCondEq > RotatingMachine > RotatingMachine.GeneratingUnit > oneOf > NuclearGeneratingUnit > Equipment.aggregateÂ¶

Title: aggregate

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The aggregate flag provides an alternative way of representing an aggregated (equivalent) element. It is applicable in cases when the dedicated classes for equivalent equipment do not have all of the attributes necessary to represent the required level of detail. In case the flag is set to âtrueâ the single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modelled together as an aggregate equivalent obtained by a network reduction procedure. Examples would be power transformers or synchronous machines operating in parallel modelled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine.
The attribute is not used for EquivalentBranch, EquivalentShunt and EquivalentInjection.

Title: normallyInService

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: Specifies the availability of the equipment under normal operating conditions. True means the equipment is available for topology processing, which determines if the equipment is energized or not. False means that the equipment is treated by network applications as if it is not in the model.

6.5.3.34. Property RegulatingCondEq > RotatingMachine > RotatingMachine.GeneratingUnit > oneOf > NuclearGeneratingUnit > IdentifiedObject.mRIDÂ¶

Title: mRID

Type

string

Required

No

Description: Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended. For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

6.5.4.4. Property RegulatingCondEq > RotatingMachine > RotatingMachine.GeneratingUnit > oneOf > WindGeneratingUnit > GeneratingUnit.governorSCDÂ¶

Title: governorSCD

Type

object or number

Required

No

Same definition as

InefficientBatteryUnit.efficiencyDischarge

Description: Governor Speed Changer Droop. This is the change in generator power output divided by the change in frequency normalized by the nominal power of the generator and the nominal frequency and expressed in percent and negated. A positive value of speed change droop provides additional generator output upon a drop in frequency.

6.5.4.30. Property RegulatingCondEq > RotatingMachine > RotatingMachine.GeneratingUnit > oneOf > WindGeneratingUnit > Equipment.aggregateÂ¶

Title: aggregate

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The aggregate flag provides an alternative way of representing an aggregated (equivalent) element. It is applicable in cases when the dedicated classes for equivalent equipment do not have all of the attributes necessary to represent the required level of detail. In case the flag is set to âtrueâ the single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modelled together as an aggregate equivalent obtained by a network reduction procedure. Examples would be power transformers or synchronous machines operating in parallel modelled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine.
The attribute is not used for EquivalentBranch, EquivalentShunt and EquivalentInjection.

Title: mRID

Type

string

Required

No

Description: Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

A positive value of speed change droop provides additional generator output upon a drop in frequency.

6.5.5.30. Property RegulatingCondEq > RotatingMachine > RotatingMachine.GeneratingUnit > oneOf > ThermalGeneratingUnit > Equipment.aggregateÂ¶

Title: aggregate

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The aggregate flag provides an alternative way of representing an aggregated (equivalent) element. It is applicable in cases when the dedicated classes for equivalent equipment do not have all of the attributes necessary to represent the required level of detail. In case the flag is set to âtrueâ the single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modelled together as an aggregate equivalent obtained by a network reduction procedure. Examples would be power transformers or synchronous machines operating in parallel modelled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine.
The attribute is not used for EquivalentBranch, EquivalentShunt and EquivalentInjection.

Title: mRID

Type

string

Required

Description: Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

6.8. Property RegulatingCondEq > RotatingMachine > SynchronousMachine.ikkÂ¶

Title: ikk

Type

object or number

Required

No

Same definition as

ExternalNetworkInjection.maxInitialSymShCCurrent

Description: Steady-state short-circuit current (in A for the profile) of generator with compound excitation during 3-phase short circuit.

  • Ikk=0: Generator with no compound excitation.

  • Ikk<>0: Generator with compound excitation. Ikk is used to calculate the minimum steady-state short-circuit current for generators with compound excitation. (4.6.1.2 in IEC 60909-0:2001). Used only for single fed short circuit on a generator. (4.3.4.2. in IEC 60909-0:2001).

6.54. Property RegulatingCondEq > RotatingMachine > Equipment.aggregateÂ¶

Title: aggregate

Type

boolean

Required

No

Description: The aggregate flag provides an alternative way of representing an aggregated (equivalent) element. It is applicable in cases when the dedicated classes for equivalent equipment do not have all of the attributes necessary to represent the required level of detail. In case the flag is set to âtrueâ the single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modelled together as an aggregate equivalent obtained by a network reduction procedure. Examples would be power transformers or synchronous machines operating in parallel modelled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine.
The attribute is not used for EquivalentBranch, EquivalentShunt and EquivalentInjection.
